<h4 id="introduction">Introduction</h4>
<p>We introduce a structure on a smooth manifold that allows to assign vectors in each 
tangent space a length and angle between vectors in the same tangent space, also called
inner product structure.</p>

<h4 id="definition-1-metrics">Definition 1: Metrics</h4>
<p>A metric on a smooth manifold \((M,O,\mathscr{A})\) is a (0,2)-tensor field.</p>
